Gerald J. Ford J.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 7:53 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Ford Financial Fund, L.P.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Gerald J. Ford J.D.General Partner and Co-Managing Member, Ford Financial Fund, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships72--
Background

		Mr. Gerald J. Ford, also known as Jerry, J.D., serves as a General Partner and Co-Managing Member of Ford Financial Fund, L.P. Mr. Ford served as the Chief Executive Officer of First Acceptance Corporation from 1996 to 2002 and Chairman of the Board of First Acceptance Corporation from 1996 to 2010. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Citibank (West) BanCorp. Inc. since 1998. Mr. Ford served as the Chief Executive Officer, Chairman and Director since ... 1994 of Golden State BanCorp. Inc. and Golden State Holdings Inc. from September 1998 to 2002. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Hilltop Holdings Inc. since December 31, 2009 until March 11, 2010 and also served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer from January 1, 2010 until March 11, 2010. Mr. Ford served as the Chief Executive Officer at Liberte Investors Inc. until July 2002. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of California Federal Bank, from October 1994 to November 2002 and California Federal Preferred Capital Corporation, from November 1996 to November 2002. Mr. Ford served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of First United Bank Group, Inc., until its sale in 1994. He is a banking and financial institutions entrepreneur and private investor and is involved in numerous mergers and acquisitions of private and public sector financial institutions, primarily in the Southwest United States, for over the 35 years. In that capacity, Mr. Ford acquired and consolidated more than 30 commercial banks from 1975 to 1993. During that period, he also led investment consortiums that acquired numerous financial institutions, forming in succession, First Gibraltar Bank, FSB, First Madison Bank, FSB and First Nationwide Bank. Mr. Ford has acquired, managed and sold banking businesses and other financial services companies for over 40 years. He has been the Chairman at Hilltop Holdings Inc. since August 01, 2007 and Director since June 30, 2005. Mr. Ford has been the Chairman of the Board and Director of First Acceptance Corp., since its formation in August 1996. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Directors at Fremont General Corporation. Mr. Ford has been the Non-Executive Chairman of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc. since January 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Freeport-McMoRan Inc. since 2000 and served as its Lead Independent Director from June 25, 2013 to December 2015. Mr. Ford has been a Director of Scientific Games Corporation since September 14, 2005 and Affordable Residential Communities Inc. since June 30, 2005. He serves as a Trustee of Southern Methodist University. Mr. Ford serves on the Executive Board of Dedman School of Law at S.M.U. He has served as chairman of the board of PlainsCapital Corporation since 2012. Mr. Ford serves as a Trustee of Southwestern Medical Foundation, Childrens Medical Foundation and Dallas Citizen's Council. He is a Member of the Board of Overseers of Weill Medical College and Graduate School of Medical Sciences of Cornell University. Mr. Ford serves as a Director of First Nationwide Holdings Inc., Mechanics Bank and Auto One Acceptance Corporation. He has been a Director of SWS Group, Inc. since July 29, 2011. Mr. Ford served as the Chairman of Flexpoint Ford, LLC. He was the Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Southern Methodist University. Mr. Ford served as the Chairman of the Board of Fremont Investment & Loan. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Triad Financial SM LLC until June 6, 2007 and served as its Co-Chairman. Mr. Ford served as Chairman of the Board of Real Industry, Inc. since May 22, 2007. He served as the Chairman of First Nationwide Mortgage Corporation from October 1994 to November 2002 and previously served as Chairman of Pacific Capital Bancorp until its sale on December 1, 2012. Mr. Ford served as a Director at Santa Barbara Bank & Trust, National Association since April 2010. He served as a Director of McMoRan Exploration Co., from 1998 to June 2013. Mr. Ford served as a Director of California Federal Bank, from October 1994 to November 2002 and California Federal Preferred Capital Corporation, from November 1996 to November 2002. He served as a Director of AmeriCredit Corp., from June 2, 2003 to August 2004. Mr. Ford served as a Director of Golden State Financial Corporation. He served as a Director of General Motors Financial Company, Inc., from June 2, 2003 to August 2004. Mr. Ford served as a Director of FCX. He served as a Director of Signature Group Holdings Inc. since May 22, 2007. Mr. Ford served as a Director of First Nationwide Mortgage Corporation. He has banking industry experience and educational background with expertise in financial, accounting and regulatory matters. In 1995, Mr. Ford was named a Distinguished Alumni of S.M.U. He received a J.D. from S.M.U. Dedman School of Law in 1969 and a B.A. in Economics from Southern Methodist University in 1966.Read Full Background




